<subSubSection lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="386" pageId="10" pageNumber="385" type="materials_examined">
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1734,2011]" pageId="10" pageNumber="385">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,448,1770,1795]" pageId="10" pageNumber="385">
<typeStatus box="[199,308,1770,1795]" pageId="10" pageNumber="385">Holotype</typeStatus>
description
</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[463,674,1770,1795]" pageId="10" pageNumber="385">Head and thorax.</emphasis>
Structural features of head and thorax much as described above for 
<taxonomicName authority="Silva &amp; Cavichioli &amp; Takiya &amp; Mejdalani, 2018" authorityName="Silva &amp; Cavichioli &amp; Takiya &amp; Mejdalani" authorityYear="2018" box="[151,260,1806,1830]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Acrogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="385" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="falcata" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[151,260,1806,1830]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="385">A. falcata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[267,356,1806,1831]" pageId="10" pageNumber="385" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[267,356,1806,1831]" pageId="10" pageNumber="385">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, except crown length approximately 9/10 interocular width.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1437,1734,2011]" lastBlockId="11.[151,1436,151,248]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="386" pageId="10" pageNumber="385">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,272,1842,1867]" pageId="10" pageNumber="385">Color.</emphasis>
Crown (
<figureCitation box="[372,454,1842,1867]" captionStart="FIGURES52–58" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1542,1565]" captionTargetBox="[173,1411,318,1498]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1435,301,1521]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES52–58. Acrogonialuizi sp. nov. 52, body, male holotype (QCAZ),dorsal view (total length 9.8mm); 53, body,male holotype, lateral view; 54–58, male genitalia:54, pygofer, lateral view; 55, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 56, styles and connective, dorsal view; 57, aedeagus, lateral view; 58, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 54 = 1 mm; 55–58 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155383/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="385">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
) yellowish-green with dark brown to black lines on coronal, frontogenal, and temporal sutures, with pair of irregular dark brown to black stripes parallel to anterior margin and joining each other apically; pronotum (
<figureCitation box="[378,459,1914,1939]" captionStart="FIGURES52–58" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1542,1565]" captionTargetBox="[173,1411,318,1498]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1435,301,1521]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES52–58. Acrogonialuizi sp. nov. 52, body, male holotype (QCAZ),dorsal view (total length 9.8mm); 53, body,male holotype, lateral view; 54–58, male genitalia:54, pygofer, lateral view; 55, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 56, styles and connective, dorsal view; 57, aedeagus, lateral view; 58, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 54 = 1 mm; 55–58 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155383/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="385">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
) with anterior portion yellowish-green, remainder mostly yellow; mesonotum (
<figureCitation box="[1347,1428,1914,1939]" captionStart="FIGURES52–58" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1542,1565]" captionTargetBox="[173,1411,318,1498]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1435,301,1521]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES52–58. Acrogonialuizi sp. nov. 52, body, male holotype (QCAZ),dorsal view (total length 9.8mm); 53, body,male holotype, lateral view; 54–58, male genitalia:54, pygofer, lateral view; 55, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 56, styles and connective, dorsal view; 57, aedeagus, lateral view; 58, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 54 = 1 mm; 55–58 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155383/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="385">Fig. 52</figureCitation>
) brownish-green with pair of basal, dark brown to black markings with yellow borders; apex yellow. Forewing mostly greenish-yellow, except apical membranous area. Face and lateral and ventral portions of thorax (
<figureCitation box="[1345,1428,1986,2011]" captionStart="FIGURES52–58" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1542,1565]" captionTargetBox="[173,1411,318,1498]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1435,301,1521]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES52–58. Acrogonialuizi sp. nov. 52, body, male holotype (QCAZ),dorsal view (total length 9.8mm); 53, body,male holotype, lateral view; 54–58, male genitalia:54, pygofer, lateral view; 55, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 56, styles and connective, dorsal view; 57, aedeagus, lateral view; 58, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 54 = 1 mm; 55–58 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155383/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="385">Fig. 53</figureCitation>
) mostly yellow; superior portion of frons, dorsolateral carina of pronotum [dorsopleural carina 
<emphasis box="[1213,1275,153,176]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="386">sensu</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Young" box="[1283,1425,151,176]" pageId="11" pageNumber="386" refString="Young, D. A. (1968) Taxonomic study of the Cicadellinae (Homoptera: Cicadellidae). Part 1. Proconiini. Bulletin of the United States National Museum, 261, 1 - 287. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 20869" type="journal article" year="1968">Young 1968</bibRefCitation>
], mesepisternum, and mesepimeron with irregular dark brown stripe; labium, labrum, and legs (
<figureCitation box="[1255,1340,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES52–58" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1542,1565]" captionTargetBox="[173,1411,318,1498]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1435,301,1521]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES52–58. Acrogonialuizi sp. nov. 52, body, male holotype (QCAZ),dorsal view (total length 9.8mm); 53, body,male holotype, lateral view; 54–58, male genitalia:54, pygofer, lateral view; 55, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 56, styles and connective, dorsal view; 57, aedeagus, lateral view; 58, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 54 = 1 mm; 55–58 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155383/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="386">Fig. 53</figureCitation>
) mostly yellowish-brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
