<subSubSection lastPageId="12" lastPageNumber="387" pageId="11" pageNumber="386" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1671,2020]" pageId="11" pageNumber="386">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,376,1671,1696]" pageId="11" pageNumber="386">Male genitalia.</emphasis>
Pygofer (
<figureCitation box="[485,568,1671,1696]" captionStart="FIGURES52–58" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1542,1565]" captionTargetBox="[173,1411,318,1498]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1435,301,1521]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES52–58. Acrogonialuizi sp. nov. 52, body, male holotype (QCAZ),dorsal view (total length 9.8mm); 53, body,male holotype, lateral view; 54–58, male genitalia:54, pygofer, lateral view; 55, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 56, styles and connective, dorsal view; 57, aedeagus, lateral view; 58, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 54 = 1 mm; 55–58 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155383/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="386">Fig. 54</figureCitation>
), in lateral view, strongly produced posteriorly and ventrally. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[159,243,1707,1732]" captionStart="FIGURES52–58" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1542,1565]" captionTargetBox="[173,1411,318,1498]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1435,301,1521]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES52–58. Acrogonialuizi sp. nov. 52, body, male holotype (QCAZ),dorsal view (total length 9.8mm); 53, body,male holotype, lateral view; 54–58, male genitalia:54, pygofer, lateral view; 55, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 56, styles and connective, dorsal view; 57, aedeagus, lateral view; 58, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 54 = 1 mm; 55–58 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155383/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="386">Fig. 55</figureCitation>
), in ventral view, subtriangular; basal half expanded laterally, then tapering gradually towards distal half; latter narrow, appearing articulated with basal half; in lateral view, plate not extending as far posteriorly as pygofer apex, distal half directed dorsally, forming angle with basal half. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[1043,1128,1779,1804]" captionStart="FIGURES52–58" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1542,1565]" captionTargetBox="[173,1411,318,1498]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1435,301,1521]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES52–58. Acrogonialuizi sp. nov. 52, body, male holotype (QCAZ),dorsal view (total length 9.8mm); 53, body,male holotype, lateral view; 54–58, male genitalia:54, pygofer, lateral view; 55, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 56, styles and connective, dorsal view; 57, aedeagus, lateral view; 58, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 54 = 1 mm; 55–58 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155383/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="386">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, T-shaped; stalk narrow, with dorsal median keel, expanded apically; arms robust. Style (
<figureCitation box="[1042,1127,1815,1840]" captionStart="FIGURES52–58" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1542,1565]" captionTargetBox="[173,1411,318,1498]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1435,301,1521]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES52–58. Acrogonialuizi sp. nov. 52, body, male holotype (QCAZ),dorsal view (total length 9.8mm); 53, body,male holotype, lateral view; 54–58, male genitalia:54, pygofer, lateral view; 55, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 56, styles and connective, dorsal view; 57, aedeagus, lateral view; 58, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 54 = 1 mm; 55–58 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155383/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="386">Fig. 56</figureCitation>
), in dorsal view, extending posteriorly farther than apex of connective, attaining base of distal half of subgenital plate; with preapical lobe; apex acute. Aedeagus (
<figureCitation box="[411,493,1887,1912]" captionStart="FIGURES52–58" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1542,1565]" captionTargetBox="[173,1411,318,1498]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1435,301,1521]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES52–58. Acrogonialuizi sp. nov. 52, body, male holotype (QCAZ),dorsal view (total length 9.8mm); 53, body,male holotype, lateral view; 54–58, male genitalia:54, pygofer, lateral view; 55, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 56, styles and connective, dorsal view; 57, aedeagus, lateral view; 58, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 54 = 1 mm; 55–58 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155383/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="386">Fig. 57</figureCitation>
) symmetrical; shaft, in lateral view, broad basally and with small dorsal projection; apex bifid, with pair of conspicuous, elongate slender hook-like processes. Anal tube (
<figureCitation box="[1129,1211,1923,1948]" captionStart="FIGURES52–58" captionStartId="11.[151,264,1542,1565]" captionTargetBox="[173,1411,318,1498]" captionTargetId="figure@11.[151,1435,301,1521]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="FIGURES52–58. Acrogonialuizi sp. nov. 52, body, male holotype (QCAZ),dorsal view (total length 9.8mm); 53, body,male holotype, lateral view; 54–58, male genitalia:54, pygofer, lateral view; 55, valve and subgenital plates, ventral view; 56, styles and connective, dorsal view; 57, aedeagus, lateral view; 58, anal tube, lateral view. Scale bars: 54 = 1 mm; 55–58 = 0.5 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155383/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="386">Fig. 58</figureCitation>
) without processes; basal apodemes directed ventrally.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,1671,2020]" box="[199,1437,1995,2020]" pageId="11" pageNumber="386">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,1995,2020]" pageId="11" pageNumber="386">Female</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[305,423,1995,2020]" pageId="11" pageNumber="386">Genitalia.</emphasis>
Sternite VII (
<figureCitation box="[593,733,1995,2020]" captionStart="FIGURES 59–66" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1879,1902]" captionTargetBox="[172,1415,574,1835]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[150,1436,553,1858]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 59–66. Acrogonia luizi sp. nov., female genitalia: 59–60, sternite VII, ventral view (macerated and unmacerated specimen, respectively); 61, valvifer Iand valvula I,lateral view (the valvifer is dislocated anterad); 62, valvifers I and valvulae I, ventral view; 63, dorsal sculptured area; 64, apex of valvula I; 65, basal portion of valvula I showing ventral interlocking device; 66, ventral sculptured area.Scale bars:59 = 1 mm;61–62 = 0.5mm.BCR = basal curvature; DLB = dorsal lobe;VID = ventral interlocking device." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155385/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="386">Figs. 59–60</figureCitation>
) bilobed; posterior margin with deep median emargination.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="12" pageNumber="387">
Pygofer, in lateral view, produced posteriorly; apex obtuse. Valvifer I (
<figureCitation box="[975,1115,151,176]" captionStart="FIGURES 59–66" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1879,1902]" captionTargetBox="[172,1415,574,1835]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[150,1436,553,1858]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 59–66. Acrogonia luizi sp. nov., female genitalia: 59–60, sternite VII, ventral view (macerated and unmacerated specimen, respectively); 61, valvifer Iand valvula I,lateral view (the valvifer is dislocated anterad); 62, valvifers I and valvulae I, ventral view; 63, dorsal sculptured area; 64, apex of valvula I; 65, basal portion of valvula I showing ventral interlocking device; 66, ventral sculptured area.Scale bars:59 = 1 mm;61–62 = 0.5mm.BCR = basal curvature; DLB = dorsal lobe;VID = ventral interlocking device." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155385/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="387">Figs. 61–62</figureCitation>
), in ventral view, expanded apically, with posterior margin truncate. Valvula I (
<figureCitation box="[720,856,188,213]" captionStart="FIGURES 59–66" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1879,1902]" captionTargetBox="[172,1415,574,1835]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[150,1436,553,1858]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 59–66. Acrogonia luizi sp. nov., female genitalia: 59–60, sternite VII, ventral view (macerated and unmacerated specimen, respectively); 61, valvifer Iand valvula I,lateral view (the valvifer is dislocated anterad); 62, valvifers I and valvulae I, ventral view; 63, dorsal sculptured area; 64, apex of valvula I; 65, basal portion of valvula I showing ventral interlocking device; 66, ventral sculptured area.Scale bars:59 = 1 mm;61–62 = 0.5mm.BCR = basal curvature; DLB = dorsal lobe;VID = ventral interlocking device." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155385/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="387">Figs. 61–62</figureCitation>
), in ventral view, with basal portion (BCR) strongly curved outwards; in lateral view, without ventral projection or lobe; basal half with small dorsal lobe (DLB); ventral interlocking device (VID) short, located on basal half of blade; dorsal sculptured area (
<figureCitation box="[1288,1428,260,285]" captionStart="FIGURES 59–66" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1879,1902]" captionTargetBox="[172,1415,574,1835]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[150,1436,553,1858]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 59–66. Acrogonia luizi sp. nov., female genitalia: 59–60, sternite VII, ventral view (macerated and unmacerated specimen, respectively); 61, valvifer Iand valvula I,lateral view (the valvifer is dislocated anterad); 62, valvifers I and valvulae I, ventral view; 63, dorsal sculptured area; 64, apex of valvula I; 65, basal portion of valvula I showing ventral interlocking device; 66, ventral sculptured area.Scale bars:59 = 1 mm;61–62 = 0.5mm.BCR = basal curvature; DLB = dorsal lobe;VID = ventral interlocking device." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155385/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="387">Figs. 63–64</figureCitation>
) extending from basal portion of blade to apex, formed mostly by scale-like processes arranged in oblique lines; ventral sculptured area (
<figureCitation box="[430,515,332,357]" captionStart="FIGURES 59–66" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1879,1902]" captionTargetBox="[172,1415,574,1835]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[150,1436,553,1858]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 59–66. Acrogonia luizi sp. nov., female genitalia: 59–60, sternite VII, ventral view (macerated and unmacerated specimen, respectively); 61, valvifer Iand valvula I,lateral view (the valvifer is dislocated anterad); 62, valvifers I and valvulae I, ventral view; 63, dorsal sculptured area; 64, apex of valvula I; 65, basal portion of valvula I showing ventral interlocking device; 66, ventral sculptured area.Scale bars:59 = 1 mm;61–62 = 0.5mm.BCR = basal curvature; DLB = dorsal lobe;VID = ventral interlocking device." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155385/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="387">Fig. 66</figureCitation>
) restricted to apical portion, formed mostly by scale-like processes; blade apex acute, dentiform (
<figureCitation box="[349,487,367,392]" captionStart="FIGURES 59–66" captionStartId="13.[151,264,1879,1902]" captionTargetBox="[172,1415,574,1835]" captionTargetId="figure@13.[150,1436,553,1858]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURES 59–66. Acrogonia luizi sp. nov., female genitalia: 59–60, sternite VII, ventral view (macerated and unmacerated specimen, respectively); 61, valvifer Iand valvula I,lateral view (the valvifer is dislocated anterad); 62, valvifers I and valvulae I, ventral view; 63, dorsal sculptured area; 64, apex of valvula I; 65, basal portion of valvula I showing ventral interlocking device; 66, ventral sculptured area.Scale bars:59 = 1 mm;61–62 = 0.5mm.BCR = basal curvature; DLB = dorsal lobe;VID = ventral interlocking device." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/1155385/files/figure.png" pageId="12" pageNumber="387">Figs. 61, 64</figureCitation>
). Valvula II, in lateral view, with dorsal margin convex; preapical prominence strong and apex obtuse, apical margin between them concave; about 18 teeth distributed continuously on posterior 3/4 of dorsal margin, most teeth triangular with ascending portion (= anterior edge) short, descending portion (posterior edge) long; blade with ducts extending to apical portion and to teeth or terminating below latter. Gonoplac, in lateral view, with basal half narrow and apical half distinctly expanded; apex obtuse.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="12" pageNumber="387">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,475,548,573]" pageId="12" pageNumber="387">Intraspecific variation.</emphasis>
The disc of the pronotum varies from yellow to dark green, whereas the forewings vary from greenish-yellow to dark green. Some variation may be due to fading of coloration in preserved specimens.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="12" pageNumber="387" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="12.[151,1437,151,933]" pageId="12" pageNumber="387">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,655,680]" pageId="12" pageNumber="387">Etymology.</emphasis>
The new species name, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Silva &amp; Cavichioli &amp; Takiya &amp; Mejdalani" authorityYear="2018" box="[613,661,656,680]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Acrogonia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="387" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="luizi">
<emphasis box="[613,661,656,680]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="387">luizi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, is given in honor of our colleague and friend Mr. Luiz A. A. Costa (Departamento de Entomologia, Museu Nacional, 
<collectionCode box="[723,791,693,716]" country="Brazil" httpUri="http://grbio.org/cool/qstz-adte" name="Universidade Federal Rural do Rio de Janeiro" pageId="12" pageNumber="387">UFRJ</collectionCode>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[803,970,692,717]" country="Brazil" name="Rio de Janeiro" pageId="12" pageNumber="387">Rio de Janeiro</collectingRegion>
) in recognition of his contribution to our knowledge of the mirids, tingids, and other heteropterans.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
